[1] Brazil (Mato Grosso)
Date: Sun 7 Jun 2009
Source: Diario de Cuiaba [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.diariodecuiaba.com.br/detalhe.php?cod=348824>


Cuiaba this year [2009] has 7000 recorded dengue [cases]. According
to the latest data from the Municipal Secretariat of Health [SMS],
there are currently 6904 [dengue] cases reported and confirmed.
Although there is over 90 percent recuperation, a brief comparison
indicates that the Cuiaba situation is alarming. In less than a year,
there already have been more than double the cases reported in all of
2003, when the city recorded about 3000 dengue cases.

The reason may be the reintroduction of dengue virus serotype 2, says
the manager of the Disease Surveillance and Transmissible Diseases of
SMS, Flavia Guimaraes Duarte. "We do not know exactly what happened,
but this may be a factor for cases of greater numbers this year
[2009]. Now, during this season, the cases tend to fall because of
the dry season, but the expectation was for not so many deaths," he explained.

Dengue virus serotype 2 is a more dangerous type of dengue virus and
was out of circulation since 2003, indicated Guimaraes. This year
[2009], the state Secretariat of Health (SES) confirmed its return.
This may explain why the children have been frequent victims of fatal
disease, because they had no contact with the virus before. The
previous contact [infection] generates an immune resistance, but the
youngest children obviously had no opportunity to develop it, stated Flavia.

--
