[2] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Wed 3 Jun 2009
Source: Fonte: Estadao [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,ba-diz-ja-ter-registrado-dengue-em-90-dos-municipios,380959,0.htm>


The Secretariat of Health of Bahia (SESAB) reported that dengue has
infected people in 90.6 percent of the 417 Bahia municipalities this
year [2009], but the rate of infection has decreased.

For the totals for the period between 1 Jan-22 May [2009], the
reports of the classic forms of the disease reached 82 402 in the
state, a number 220 percent greater than that recorded in the same
period last year (28 432) [2008]. Also included were 1415 suspected
cases of more serious forms of dengue and 55 confirmed deaths due to
the disease. An additional 54 cases are being investigated.

Despite the data, the totals of the advance of dengue indicated a
fall in the rate of infection in the population. In the week between
16-22 May 2009, 1483 new reports of the disease were recorded in
Bahia, the 2nd lowest of the year, a larger number only than that
recorded in the 1st week of 2009, when there were 1109 recorded [cases].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

