[3] Brazil (Espirito Santo)
Date: Mon 1 Jun 2009
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/cidades/mat/2009/06/01/espirito-santo-registra-39-mil-casos-26-mortes-por-dengue-este-ano-756129040.asp>


This year [2009], Esperito Santo recorded 39 000 cases of dengue and
26 deaths from the disease in the state, according to data released
this Monday [1 Jun 2009] by the state Secretariat of Health (SESA);
24 other deaths are under investigation. Municipalities with the most
confirmed recorded [dengue cases] are Sierra with 8658, Vila Velha
with 7455 cases; Vitoria (5327), Nova Venecia (3919) and Baixo Guandu (1796).

Up to last Friday [29 May 2009], according to the Secretariat, 1361
suspected serious dengue cases were reported and progressed to
recovery. Of these, 222 were confirmed as dengue with complications
and 106 as DHF. The other cases are under investigation.

Of the 26 confirmed deaths, 13 were due to DHF and were recorded in
the municipalities of Sierra, Linhares, Vila Velha, Guarapari, Nova
Venezia, Conceicao da Barra and Vitoria. The other 13 deaths,
classified as severe dengue, were in Vila Velha, Cariacica, Baixo
Guandu, Nova Venezia, Vitoria and Serra.

--
