[4] Western Hemisphere tropics
Date: Fri 5 Jun 2008
Source: Red Orbit [summarized]
<http://www.redorbit.com/news/health/1701175/scientists_develop_the_first_climatebased_model_to_predict_dengue_fever/>


[This report describes a model that uses effects of climate variables
and vegetation indices on _Aedes aegypti_ populations to predict and
mitigate dengue epidemics in the American tropics. The new model is
reported to predict dengue fever epidemics with 83 percent accuracy
up to 40 weeks in advance of an outbreak and provide information on
the magnitude of future epidemics. It will be interesting to see how
the model performs over time. - Mod.TY]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-Mail Rapporteur Susan Baekeland

